.TH "bpt.conf" "5" "2026-03-11"
.PP
.SH NAME
.PP
bpt.\&conf - configuration file for the Bedrock Package Tool
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\fBbpt.\&conf\fR configures \fBbpt\fR(1).\&
.PP
The default configuration file path is \fB/etc/bpt/bpt.\&conf\fR.\&
.PP
The file uses INI-like sections and \fBkey = value\fR entries.\&
.PP
Blank lines and comments beginning with \fB#\fR are ignored.\&
.PP
If an option is omitted, \fBbpt\fR falls back to its built-in default.\&
.PP
.SH SECTIONS
.PP
.SS [general]
.PP
\fBdefault-archs\fR
.PP
Comma-separated preferred architectures used to resolve package identifiers
that omit \fB:<arch>\fR.\&
.PP
Default:
.RS 4
\fBnoarch, host\fR
.PP
.RE
Valid values include:
.PP
.PD 0
.IP \(bu 4
\fBnoarch\fR for architecture-independent packages
.IP \(bu 4
\fBhost\fR for portable packages matching the current machine architecture
.IP \(bu 4
\fBnative\fR to prefer building locally with machine-specific optimizations
.IP \(bu 4
\fBbbuild\fR for build-definition package identifiers
.IP \(bu 4
explicit architectures such as \fBx86_64\fR, \fBaarch64\fR, or \fBriscv64gc\fR
.PD
.PP
Example:
.RS 4
\fBdefault-archs = noarch, native\fR
.PP
.RE
\fBpin-direct-pkgver\fR
.PP
Whether direct package inputs such as \fB.\&/pkg.\&bpt\fR or \fB.\&/pkg.\&bbuild\fR should
write a version-pinned world entry.\&
.PP
If \fBfalse\fR, direct package inputs behave like an unpinned request and can be
upgraded later.\& If \fBtrue\fR, the resulting world entry includes \fB@<pkgver>\fR.\&
.PP
Default:
.RS 4
\fBfalse\fR
.PP
.RE
.SS [networking]
.PP
\fButil\fR
.PP
Defines a command line for fetching \fBhttp://\fR and \fBhttps://\fR URLs.\& The command
must contain a literal \fB{}\fR placeholder where the URL should be inserted.\&
.PP
Values are split on ASCII whitespace.\& They are not shell-parsed.\&
.PP
The first configured utility found in \fB$PATH\fR is used.\&
.PP
Default:
.RS 4
\fButil = curl -f -L {}\fR
\fButil = wget -O- {}\fR
.PP
.RE
\fBprint-stderr\fR
.PP
Whether the selected network utility'\&s stderr should be shown.\&
.PP
Default:
.RS 4
\fBfalse\fR
.PP
.RE
.SS [build]
.PP
\fBunprivileged-user\fR
.PP
User name to switch to when \fBbpt\fR is asked to process a \fB.\&bbuild\fR while
running as root.\&
.PP
Default:
.RS 4
\fBbpt\fR
.PP
.RE
\fBunprivileged-group\fR
.PP
Group name to switch to when \fBbpt\fR is asked to process a \fB.\&bbuild\fR while
running as root.\&
.PP
Default:
.RS 4
\fBbpt\fR
.PP
.RE
\fBtmp\fR
.PP
Directory used for temporary build artifacts.\&
.PP
On Bedrock Linux this should normally be a globally visible path so tooling in
other strata can access it.\&
.PP
Default:
.RS 4
\fB/tmp\fR
.PP
.RE
.SS [make-repo]
.PP
\fBarchs\fR
.PP
Comma-separated architectures for which \fBbpt make-repo\fR should emit package and
index artifacts.\&
.PP
Default:
.RS 4
\fBnoarch, host, bbuild\fR
.PP
.RE
Valid values include:
.PP
.PD 0
.IP \(bu 4
\fBnoarch\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\fBhost\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\fBbbuild\fR
.IP \(bu 4
explicit architectures such as \fBx86_64\fR or \fBaarch64\fR
.PD
.PP
.SS [cache]
.PP
\fBpkg-max-days\fR
.PP
Maximum age in days for cached \fB.\&bpt\fR package files during full \fBbpt sync\fR
operations.\&
.PP
Use \fBforever\fR to disable age-based eviction, or \fB0\fR to evict immediately.\&
.PP
Default:
.RS 4
\fB90\fR
.PP
.RE
\fBsrc-max-days\fR
.PP
Maximum age in days for cached source files during full \fBbpt sync\fR operations.\&
.PP
Use \fBforever\fR to disable age-based eviction, or \fB0\fR to evict immediately.\&
.PP
Default:
.RS 4
\fB90\fR
.PP
.RE
.SH FILES
.PP
\fB/etc/bpt/bpt.\&conf\fR
.RS 4
Default configuration file.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\fBbpt\fR(1)
